It would appear from the findings that the firm should go ahead and start operating the mine. The payback period is within a reasonable timescale of four years, the internal rate of return (IRR) and the modified internal rate of return (MIRR) are significantly higher than the needed return rate of 12%, and the net present value (NPV) is positive at $1,564,660,000. Before making a final choice, it is essential to take into account a variety of additional aspects, including the state of the market, the level of competition, and any relevant regulatory concerns. 